eekends.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esleep%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20leading%20to%20restless%20nights%20and%20stressful%20dreams.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20survey%20of%201%2C750%20working%20adults%20in%20the%20US%20conducted%20by%20Each%20Night%2C%20a%20sleep%20resource%20platform%2C%20more%20than%20three-fifths%20of%20workers%20reported%20having%20a%20nightmare%20about%20their%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20common%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsigns-of-toxic-workplace-how-identify-spot-interview-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworkplace%3C%2Fa%3E%20nightmare%20is%20being%20late%20to%20work%2C%20according%20to%20an%20analysis%20of%20global%20search%20data%20conducted%20by%20the%20job%20search%20platform%20JobLeads.%20Losing%20your%20job%2C%20getting%20a%20new%20job%2C%20and%20colleague%20romances%20were%20also%20commonly%20reported%20dreams.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsilicon-valley-therapist-seeing-panic-anxiety-amid-tech-layoffs-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAnnie%20Wright%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20psychotherapist%20who%20operates%20boutique%20trauma%20therapy%20centers%20in%20California%20and%20Florida%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20dreams%20are%20worth%20analyzing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fear%20of%20being%20late%20to%20work%20can%20signify%20a%20sense%20of%20uncertainty%2C%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20doesn't%20terribly%20surprise%20me%20that%20that's%20showing%20up%20because%2C%20you%20know%2C%20we%20have%20that%20classic%20dream%20in%20college%20and%20high%20school%20of%20being%20late%20for%20a%20test%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThrough%20the%20lens%20of%20gestalt%20psychotherapy%20%E2%80%94%20a%20therapeutic%20approach%20that%20focuses%20on%20understanding%20a%20person's%20present%20experience%20%E2%80%94%20every%20element%20of%20a%20dream%2C%20from%20the%20setting%20to%20the%20people%2C%20places%2C%20and%20objects%2C%20can%20be%