%20many%20in%20Denmark%20and%20Greenland%20reeling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20heart%20of%20Trump's%20interest%20in%20Greenland%20lies%20its%20strategic%20importance%20for%20national%20security.%20The%20island%20is%20rich%20in%20minerals%20crucial%20for%20technology%20and%20defense%2C%20including%20rare%20earth%20elements%20used%20in%20mobile%20phones%2C%20electric%20vehicles%2C%20and%20weapons.%20With%20China%20dominating%20the%20global%20rare%20earth%20market%2C%20Greenland's%20reserves%20have%20become%20increasingly%20vital%20to%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20has%20been%20wanting%20to%20take%20over%20the%20island%20nation%20of%2056%2C000%20people%20since%20his%20first%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGreenland's%20location%2C%20straddling%20the%20shortest%20route%20between%20Europe%20and%20North%20America%2C%20makes%20it%20a%20critical%20spot%20for%20the%20US%20military%20and%20its%20ballistic%20missile%20early-warning%20system.%20As%20China%20and%20Russia%20expand%20their%20influence%20in%20the%20Arctic%2C%20the%20US%20seeks%20to%20maintain%20its%20dominance%20in%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBrian%20Hughes%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20National%20Security%20Council%2C%20told%20Fox%20that%20Trump%20has%20made%20it%20clear%20%26quot%3Bthe%20safety%20and%20security%20of%20Greenland%20is%20important%20to%20the%20United%20States%20as%20China%20and%20Russia%20make%20significant%20investments%20throughout%20the%20Arctic%20region.%20The%20President%20is%20committed%20to%20not%20only%20protecting%20U.S.%20interests%20in%20the%20Arctic%20but%20also%20working%20with%20Greenland%20to%20ensure%20mutual%20prosperity%20for%20both%20nations%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20was%20very%20firm%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20source%20told%20the%20Financial%20Times%2C%20describing%20Trump's%20tone%20during%20the%20phone%20call.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20a%20cold%20shower.%20Before%2C%20it%20was%20hard%20to%20take%20it%20seriously.%20But%20I%20do%20think%20it%20is%20serious%2C%20and%20potentially%20very%20dangerous.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20phone%20call%20was%20%26quot%3Bfiery%26quot%3B%20with%20one%20official%20calling%20it%20%26quot%3Bhorrendous%26quot%3B%2C%20per%20the%20Financial%20Times.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20call%20%26quot%3Butterly%20freaked%20out%26quot%3B%20the%20Danes%2C%20one%20Danish%20official%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20intent%20was%20very%20clear%2C%26quot%3B%20another%20official%20told%20the%20outlet.%20%26quot%3BThey%20want%20it.%20The%20Danes%20are%20now%20in%20crisis%20mode.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump's%20aggressive%20pursuit%20of%20Greenland%20has%20been%20met%20with%20resistance%20from%20Denmark%20and%20Greenland.%20Frederiksen%20has%20emphasised%20that%20Greenland%20is%20not%20for%20sale%2C%20and%20its%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20Mute%20Edege%2C%20has%20reiterated%20that%20the%20island's%20people%20do%20not%20want%20to%20be%20part%20of%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20repeatedly%2C%20the%20US%20says%20that%20Greenland%20is%20important%20for%20its%20national%20security.%20Despite%20Frederiksen's%20offer%20to%20increase%20the%20cooperation%20between%20Greenland%20and%20US%20on%20military%20bases%20and%20resources%2C%20Trump%20was%20aggressive%20and%20confrontational.%20Moreover%20he%20has%20not%20ruled%20out%20the%20possible%20use%20of%20military%20force%20in%20Greenland.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20purposes%20of%20National%20Security%20and%20Freedom%20throughout%20the%20World%2C%20the%20United%20States%20of%20America%20feels%20that%20the%20ownership%20and%20control%20of%20Greenland%20is%20an%20absolute%20necessity%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20wrote%20on%20Truth%20Social%20last%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResidents%20of%20Greenland%20have%20also%20expressed%20their%20distrust%20of%20Trump%20and%20his%20intentions.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20trust%20the%20guy%2C%26quot%3B%20Bilo%20Chemnitz%2C%20a%20resident%20of%20Nuuk%2C%20told%20The%20Washington%20Post.%20%26quot%3BI%20want%2